pull.title: [qt] Fix potential memory leak in newPossibleKey(ChangeCWallet *wallet)

events.body: Is it possible to change this to use a `unique_ptr` instead?

:+1: @sipa suggestion.

Correct me if I'm wrong, but from what I've seen, `WalletModelTransaction::keyChange` pointer is initialized to null, and only has a value when `newPossibleKeyChange` is called. So, in the first call, this would `delete NULL`.

Moreover, in the `~WalletModelTransaction` it also `delete keyChange` which can be null if `newPossibleKeyChange` is not called.

@sipa Sure, I'll fix!

@promag We're doing `delete NULL` all over the codebase assuming it is a no-op :-)
Yeah it's safe, can be avoided though.
But there's no reason to avoid it..

events.message: [qt] Fix potential memory leak in newPossibleKey(ChangeCWallet *wallet)

events.body: utACK 446e2610b0cd6535e623952bf22ea09ce0ed8aaf. FWIW #10244 (commit "Remove most direct bitcoin calls from qt/walletmodel.cpp") takes this cleanup further, combining key and transaction into a pending transaction object and referencing that through a unique pointer.
